description:
Previously had their pizza and fries as takeout, and liked them so much that I obviously had to dine in!

We had the fries (so good, they come with 3 dips); 
the burrata (has some pesto sauce and grilled tomatoes with some bread- it's like a chic version of bruschetta); 
the margherita pizza; and the halibut.

I guess the halibut is new on the menu and it was a serious A+. Who doesn't like a perfect buttery piece of fish on top of some delish risotto? 

Great service too. Thanks!
